      • getCondition

        public PsiExpression getCondition()
        Description copied from interface: PsiConditionalLoopStatement
        Returns the expression representing the condition of the loop. The condition is checked after every loop iteration, and iteration stops when condition evaluates to false.

        Concrete loops may or may not check the condition before the first iteration. Also, additional steps could be performed at the loop start or between the body execution and condition checking.

        Specified by:
        getCondition in interface PsiConditionalLoopStatement
        Returns:
        the expression, or null if condition is absent. The absent condition could be a legal case or incomplete statement, depending on the kind of the loop.
